{
  "stem": "13079.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in the judge-advocate section of Headquarters Third Army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, the judge-advocate section is the legal adviser to the commanding general.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My, my superior there was Colonel Cheever, who was a staff judge-advocate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was an assistant staff judge-advocate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had charge of the administration of Military Justice in Headquarters Third Army prior to being appointed to take over the prosecution of the concentration camp cases.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My contact with General Patton, whom we had to take the court martial records down to General Patton for his approval when there were general court martials that were involved.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had submitted the records to General Patton.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I had personal contact with General Patton.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now General Truskett, he succeeded General Patton.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had very little contact with General Truskett because I was in the process of prosecuting these cases at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And General Truskett was stationed down in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got all the support that the law allowed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was trying to get witnesses out of Vienna in for the trial of [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mauthausen, ?] there was a staff-judge advocate in seventh army, which was in the command of General Mark Clark.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he didn't want to let me take the witnesses out of Vienna because he felt that the Russians would fear that we were kidnapping these people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I asked to speak to General Clark and I went in and spoke to General Clark and told him what I wanted to do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he says, well, it's not going to be a mass exodus, is it?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, no, sir.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He says, we'll take them out four or five at a time and take them to Dachau, which was at Munich, and you certainly have my consent to do that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
